# Scope
Applies to all tests in `tests/`, especially API tests in `tests/api/`.

## Test structure
- Every test file starts with `test.describe()` representing the endpoint or feature.
- `describe` name must include the HTTP method and full route.
- Each `test()` validates a single behavior.
- Test names are in English and must start with `Should ...`.

## Independence and data hygiene
- No test depends on another.
- Avoid shared global state across tests.
- Clean data before creating new records.
- If a test creates data, it cleans up when needed.
- Use a dedicated test database.

## Auth setup
- Current setup lives at `tests/auth.setup.ts`.
- Admin storageState is saved to `.auth/cookies.admin.json`.
- Use it in tests via:
  - `test.use({ storageState: './.auth/cookies.admin.json' })`
- `.auth/` must not be committed.

## Future module setup pattern
When new modules are introduced:
- Register module name in `shared/repository/modules.list.ts`.
- Module name must match `modules/<module>/` folder name.
- Setup file must be `tests/setup/<module>.setup.ts`.
- StorageState must be `.auth/cookies.<module>.json`.

